MediConnect Pro — Main Features
1. Real-Time Health Monitoring
Simulated sensor readings for Heart Rate, Blood Pressure, Oxygen Saturation, and Temperature
Visual status indicators (normal/warning/danger)
Interactive vitals history chart (Chart.js)
Automated health alerts for abnormal readings
2. Doctor Consultation (Chat System)
List of available doctors with online/busy/offline status
Real-time chat interface between patient and doctor
AI-simulated doctor responses based on symptom keywords
Free 24/7 access messaging
3. Appointment Booking
Doctor selection dropdown
Date/time picker for scheduling
Symptom/notes input
Booking confirmation system
4. AI Symptom Checker
Input symptoms (e.g., "headache, fever")
Returns probability-matched conditions with severity levels
Provides basic advice and medical disclaimers
5. Medication Tracker
List of current medications with dosage info
"Take" button to mark doses as taken
Add new medications with custom names/dosages/frequency
Due-time reminders
6. Disease Outbreak Alerts
Live (simulated) outbreak data display
Shows disease name, case counts, trend, affected regions
Severity badges (High/Moderate/Low)
7. Health Education Center
Educational cards on topics like:
Balanced Diet & Nutrition
Hypertension (High BP)
Disease Outbreak Prevention
Heart Health
Click-to-expand modal articles with prevention tips
8. Emergency Services
Prominent 911/Emergency call button
Visual warning for medical emergencies
9. Dashboard Statistics
Live counters: Doctors Online, Patients Helped, Early Detections, Avg Response Time
🎨 Design & Technical Highlights
Table
Aspect	Details
UI Style	Dark glassmorphism theme with gradient accents
Responsive	Mobile-adaptive grid layout
Animations	Pulse effects, hover transitions, fade-ins
Charts	Chart.js for vitals history visualization
Backend	API-ready (localhost:5000/api) with fallback simulation
Icons	Emoji-based iconography
⚠️ Current Status
This is a frontend prototype/simulation — the health data is randomly generated, doctor responses are hardcoded keyword matching, and the backend API calls fall back to demo data when the server is unavailable.
